Musical artist

Sabrina Claudio (born September 19, 1996) is an American singer and songwriter. In late 2016, Claudio uploaded several songs to SoundCloud, before compiling a select collection as part of her debut extended play, Confidently Lost, which was released independently in March 2017.

2017 was her breakout year; her single "Unravel Me" peaked at number 22 on the Billboard Twitter Emerging Artists chart, and "Belong to You" peaked at number two and was certified Gold by the RIAA. Her debut mixtape, About Time "About Time (mixtape)"), was released on October 5; it peaked at number 13 on Billboard "Billboard (magazine)")'s Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums chart. [...] Print/export

Musical artist [...] On October 5, 2017, Claudio's debut full-length digital mixtape, About Time "About Time (mixtape)"), was officially released. The mixtape is supported by the singles "Unravel Me" and "Belong to You". From October through November 2017, Apple Music promoted Claudio as their Up Next artist, a series that focuses on breakthrough artists by documenting their journey, inspiration and influences through exclusive interviews, live performances and a mini-documentary.

On April 2, 2018, Claudio released the single "All to You" followed by "Don't Let Me Down" featuring Khalid "Khalid (American singer)") on April 4. Her debut studio album No Rain, No Flowers, was released on August 15, 2018, preceded by the single "Messages From Her". Her management is SAL&CO/Neal Atweh.

data.title: Claudiu Dumitrache - EverybodyWiki Bios & Wiki
data.snippet: Dumitrache Mihai Claudiu (born May 7, 1999) is a singer and writer from Romania. Born in Bucharest, Romania and living in Costeștii din Vale, he set the national record for the youngest author of autobiography at the age of 20. He won the special award Music Awards TV in 2016 and released the first single titled Lumea Mea (My World), composed by him on the lyrics of his mother. The biggest concert he gave was in 2016 in Iași city, when he sang in the opening of Alphaville (band), in front of over 15,000 people. [...] The Romanian Academy recognized Claudiu as a symbol for the future of intellectual creation. In July 2020, he was honored with the merit of Honorary Citizen in Costeștii din Vale for his cultural and artistic contributions to the community, for promoting the commune nationally and internationally, in contact with the United States or Belgium, proving diplomatic qualities. In May 2020, the Eurovision composer Michael James Down claims that Mihai-Claudiu have a fantastic voice and the right charisma to be an international artist. The Irish artist also mentions: Claudiu is the type of person who make things happen!. His books have been commented by several writers, artists, Romanian critics and by the press, resembling him with Arthur Rimbaud, Mihai Eminescu, George Bacovia or Alexandru [...] Artists like Michael Airington, Eb Davis, Dida Drǎgan or Michaela Rose (Arabesque) had something to say about Claudiu in the biographical book 20 he released in 2019. His biography was included in a top of Romanian books on the Books of the Year.

data.title: claudiopercussion EN - About Claudio Spieler
data.snippet:
Always striving for improvement Claudio studied with great musicians like Luis Conte, Karuna Murthy, Juan-Carlos Melian, Steve Smith, Sankha Chatterjee, Lenny Castro, Alex Acuña, Pete Lockett, Swapan Chaudhuri, Richie Gajate-Garcia, Cepillo, Rubem Dantas, Ramon Porrina, Paquito Gonzalez and Selva Ganesh.

## Concerts and Tours [...] ## Concerts and Tours

Claudio performs in a wide range of musical styles with his current ensembles: Tevana, Ragga Gröndal & The Icelandic Folk Ensemble, Ragga Gröndal Trio, World of Strings, Groovetrotters and Barokan. He has worked with many different artists including Peter Herbert, Phil Maturano, Konstantin Wecker, Peter Madsen, Daniel Pezzotti, Raquel Villegas Gomez, Maria Mezcle, Amit Chatterjee, Apratim Mayumdar, Mamadou Diabate, Studio Percussion Graz, Karen Lugo, Bitori and Abbos Kosimov; and has been invited to perform at well-known festivals like Reykjavik Jazz Festival, Percussion Festival Telfs, Flamenco Biennale Netherlands, Airwaves Iceland, Night of Percussion Graz, WOMAD Fuerteventura, Wiener Konzerthaus and many more.

## Educator and instructor [...] In 2004, he started his private studies with the renowned international percussion artist - maestro Hakim Ludin. Under Hakim Ludin´s wing he learned the language and the art of playing hand percussion. In 2008, the product of the student/maestro relationship developed into the founding of the innovative duo program called Percussion Discussion. Due to his intensive work with Hakim Ludin, Claudio has developed a comprehensive repertoire and a large amount of hand and finger techniques for different framedrums, Afrocuban and Afrobrazilian drums and Indian drums.
